summary:
Corsaro calls upon all adults to appreciate, embrace, and savor their
children&#39;s culture. He asks us to take a cue from those we hold so
precious and understand that &quot;we&#39;re all friends, right?&quot;

This collection of over forty of Anderson&#39;s most popular stories
includes &quot;The Ugly Duckling&quot;, &quot;The Red Shoes&quot;, and
&quot;The Little Match Girl.&quot;
